                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ajdæn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ajdæn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ajdanæ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>зеркало</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>mirror</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>ḱyzg kæsyn bajdydta ajdæny</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>девушка стала глядеть в зеркало</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the girl began to look in the mirror</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>96</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>arvy ajdæn lystæg pyrx nycci</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>небесное зеркало разбилось вдребезги</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the celestial mirror shattered</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 63</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>xūry ajdæn rajsta kʼūlæj æmæ ʒy kæsy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сняла со стены солнечное зеркало и смотрит в него</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>she took off a solar mirror from the wall and she is looking into it</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II 58</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>arvy ajdæny arǧaw</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сказка о небесном зеркале</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the tale of the celestial mirror</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 93</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>stur ajdænæ ærttevæntæ kodta xormæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>большое зеркало сверкало на солнце</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a large mirror sparkled in the sun</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>119</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>ḱyzg kæsyn bajdydta ajdæny</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>девушка стала глядеть в зеркало</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the girl began to look in the mirror</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>96</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>arvy ajdæn lystæg pyrx nycci</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>небесное зеркало разбилось вдребезги</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the celestial mirror shattered</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 63</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>xūry ajdæn rajsta kʼūlæj æmæ ʒy kæsy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сняла со стены солнечное зеркало и смотрит в него</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>she took off a solar mirror from the wall and she is looking into it</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II 58</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>arvy ajdæny arǧaw</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сказка о небесном зеркале</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the tale of the celestial mirror</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 93</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>stur ajdænæ ærttevæntæ kodta xormæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>большое зеркало сверкало на солнце</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a large mirror sparkled in the sun</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>119</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*ā-dayana-</w></mentioned> от <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>dī</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w>day-</w> <gloss><q>глядеть</q></gloss></mentioned>,  („гляделка“); ср. <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>ādēn</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><w>ādēnk</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>āδēnak</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w>ādēng</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 77</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 77</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>āδēnak(''δ'yn'k)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>āyəna</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>ātīna</w></mentioned>,  (ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>dyāna</w> <gloss><q>видимый</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>āyīna</w></mentioned>. Звуковая история слова может быть уточнена привлечением таких случаев стяжения группы %iауа%i, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fijjaw"/> ‘пастух’ из %ifæjau%i, fæstijæ ‘сзади’ из %ifæstæjæ%i, %izærdijæn%i ‘сердцу’ из %izærdæjæn%i, %iærtijæn%i ‘трем’ из %iærtæjæn%i и т. п.; по аналогии с этими случаями предполагаем: *%iādayana%i →*%iadæjæn%i → *%iadijæn%i → *%iadjæn%i → %iajdæn%i. Из *%iādaina%i (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>LII 9</biblScope></bibl>) имели бы *%iadīn%i, как из %iaxšaina%i- → <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxsīn"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*ā-dayana-</w></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>dī</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w>day-</w> <gloss><q>look</q></gloss></mentioned>, (“looker”): <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>ādēn</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><w>ādēnk</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>āδēnak</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w>ādēng</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 77</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 77</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>āδēnak(ˈˈδ'ynyk)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>āyəna</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>ātīna</w></mentioned>,  (cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>dyāna</w> <gloss><q>visible</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>āyīna</w></mentioned>. The sound history of the word can be refined by invoking such cases of contraction of the %iaya%i group as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fijjaw"/> ‘shepherd’ from %ifæjau%i, %ifæstijæ%i ‘behind’ from %ifæstæjæ%i, %izærdijæn%i ‘heart (dat)’ from %izærdæjæn%i, %iærtijæn%i ‘three (dat)’ from %iærtæjæn%i and so on; by analogy with these cases, we assume: *%iādayana%i →*%iadæjæn%i → *%iadijæn%i → *%iadjæn%i → %iajdæn%i. From *%iādaina%i (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>LII 9</biblScope></bibl>) we would have had *%iadīn%i, as from %iaxšaina%i- → <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxsīn"/>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>